that runs anything
that we can go after.

23:58.103 --> 24:06.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEON PANETTA: Well, you're
right, in the sense
that, just as we have learned
how to confront

24:06.812 --> 24:12.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
terrorist groups and try to
track them and
go after their planning for
possible attacks

24:12.518 --> 24:15.054 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in this country, they have
learned as well.

24:15.087 --> 24:22.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have learned, you know, a
lot of our
technology, our process, how we
operate. And

24:22.361 --> 24:29.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the result is that they operate
much more
in a lone wolf fashion, in the
sense that,

24:29.034 --> 24:38.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you know, they do outreach, they
have individuals
that are well-placed, but they
minimize the

24:38.444 --> 24:42.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
contacts. They minimize the
planning. And
that makes them even a greater
threat.

24:42.748 --> 24:45.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Secretary Leon
Panetta,
thanks so much for joining us.

24:45.317 --> 24:48.420 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LEON PANETTA: Thank you very
