months just waiting to make the
treacherous

42:19.237 --> 42:25.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
journey across the Aegean Sea to
Lesbos. And
they had to try on four
different occasions.

42:25.543 --> 42:29.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They were caught by the Turkish
authorities
twice. Once, they didn't want to
get in because

42:29.480 --> 42:31.215 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they thought it was too
dangerous.

42:31.249 --> 42:35.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can only imagine making this
journey with
a 2-year-old child. But they
finally made

42:35.920 --> 42:42.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it on the fourth try. And then
the other couple,
Ramy and Suhila, they were able
to get into

42:42.193 --> 42:46.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a rubber boat, but the motor
stopped working
in the middle of the Aegean Sea.
They had

42:46.898 --> 42:52.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to wait for very a nerve-racking
hour-and-a-half,
until, finally, it started
working again.

42:52.703 --> 42:57.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so you can only imagine just
how stressful
this is. One of the couples who
wasn't able

42:57.975 --> 43:04.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to join us, Hari, they have two
small children.
One of their children stopped
talking for

43:04.315 --> 43:09.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
