43:09.587 --> 43:11.389 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the night.

43:11.422 --> 43:16.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this is really the human
cost of this
refugee crisis. And I think
hearing from these

43:16.260 --> 43:22.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
families personally, I think
that brought
that home in a way that, you
know, is in a

43:22.633 --> 43:24.368 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
way that we don't often hear.

43:24.402 --> 43:29.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I really was grateful that
we were able
to hear about their experiences
firsthand.

43:29.273 --> 43:31.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: What are that
are plans
now? Are they going to stay in
Italy?

43:31.476 --> 43:35.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATIE COURIC: They are going to
stay in Italy.
They're learning to speak
Italian. Their children

43:36.013 --> 43:40.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are in school or in day care.
They're hoping
they're going to find some kind
of employment.

43:40.952 --> 43:47.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But unemployment is 12 in Italy,
37 percent,
if you can believe it, for
younger people.

43:47.391 --> 43:51.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why they were hoping to
go to France
or Germany. But I think, because
they have

43:51.662 --> 43:56.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been so embraced, Catholic
Charities is caring
for them, they have given them a
place to

43:56.400 --> 44:01.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stay, they're so grateful for
their security,
I think they're going to try to
build a new

44:01.072 --> 44:06.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
life in Italy and hopefully,
they say, return
to Syria one day, if they can.

44:06.244 --> 44:10.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Yahoo News
global anchor
Katie Couric, thanks so much for
joining us.

44:10.948 --> 44:18.122 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KATIE COURIC: Thanks, Hari.

44:18.155 --> 44:24.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: As you have
likely heard
by now, Malia Obama has decided
to take a

44:24.662 --> 44:29.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
